olive oil
½ carrot
1 cucumber
1 packet pork loin steaks
¾ cup water
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet couscous
1 bag baby spinach leaves
20 g butter
1 packet Mango Chilli Sauce
3 clove garlic
1 sachet Mild North Indian Spice Blend
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Finely chop garlic. Grate carrot (see
ingredients). Grate cucumber and squeeze out
excess liquid using paper towel or a clean cloth.
• In a medium bowl, combine pork loin steaks,
mild North Indian spice blend, a pinch of salt
and pepper and a drizzle of olive oil. Set aside.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat. Cook 1/2 the garlic until
fragrant, 1 minute.
• Transfer garlic oil to a small bowl. Add
cucumber and Greek-style yoghurt to garlic
mixture. Stir to combine, season to taste and
set aside.

• In a medium saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat.
• Add carrot and remaining garlic and cook,
stirring, until softened, 2-3 minutes. Add the
water, chicken-style stock powder and a pinch
of salt and bring to the boil. Add couscous, stir
to combine.
• Cover with a lid and remove from heat. Set aside
until all the water has absorbed, 5 minutes. Fluff
up with a fork.
• Add baby spinach leaves and the butter and
stir until melted.

• Meanwhile, return frying pan to medium-high
heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook pork loin steaks until
cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side (cook in
batches if your pan is getting crowded).

• Remove pan from heat and add mango chilli
sauce and a splash of water and turn to coat.
• Transfer to a plate, cover and rest for 5 minutes.

• Slice pork steak.
• Divide carrot couscous and mango chilli-glazed
pork steak between plates.
• Top with cucumber raita. Enjoy!